The Tunisian people are characterized by strong ideologies that have always dominated them since the conquests of Islam until the end of the Umayyad regime. It doesn’t affect the young generation, which, according to Tawfiq Saqer al-Mubarak, is characterized by a high degree of devotion to God and religious righteousness with a high degree of freedom from rigid customs.
It is worth mentioning that some scholars declare their lack of knowledge in recounting the history chronologically, according to Abd al-Fattah Mahmoud al-Masri, because the historical curtains are intertwined from their birth and throughout the generations.
Al-Masri thought that the events took place in Tunisia were an alive part of Africa, but with its own historical mode. It was controlled by the late Legislatures of the Banu Hafs until the climate and the emergence of the Berber uprisings and the rebellion of the Hamadites, the Hamadides.
The liberation movement was one of the reasons behind the continuation of the influence of Hafsids. After the French occupation, the National Liberation Front emerged to win the independence war.
